# ‚ûï How to Add a New Model

This project uses a **plugin-based model system**.  
To add a new model, follow these steps.

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a model file

Create a new file inside the `models/` folder.

Example:
models/my_model.py

python
Copy code

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Write the model class

Your model file **must look like this**:

```python
from core.base_model import BaseModel
from core.registry import register_model

class MyModel(BaseModel):
    name = "my-model"   # unique model name

    def load(self):
        # load weights OR connect to API here
        print("MyModel loaded")

    def generate(self, prompt: str) -> str:
        # take prompt and return text
        return f"Response: {prompt}"

# REQUIRED: register the model
register_model(MyModel)
3Ô∏è‚É£ Import the model (MANDATORY)
Add your model import in:

bash
Copy code
models/__init__.py
Example:

python
Copy code
from models.my_model import MyModel
‚ö†Ô∏è If you skip this step, the model will NOT appear.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Run the app
From project root:

bash
Copy code
python -m app.main
Your model will now appear in the selection list.

‚úÖ Checklist
 File created in models/

 Inherits BaseModel

 Has unique name

 Implements load() and generate()

 Calls register_model()

 Imported in models/__init__.py

Done ‚úÖ

